  "prompt": "If he's over me then why does he send me random messages and pictures?",
  "response": "It can be confusing when someone who has supposedly moved on still reaches out to you. Here are a few possibilities for why he might be sending you random messages and pictures:\n\n1. **Nostalgia**: He might feel nostalgic about your past relationship or the good times you shared, prompting him to reach out.\n\n2. **Friendship**: He could want to maintain a friendship and keep in touch, even if the romantic aspect is over for him.\n\n3. **Testing Waters**: He might be unsure about his feelings and is trying to gauge your reaction to see if there\u2019s still a connection.\n\n4. **Loneliness**: Sometimes people reach out when they\u2019re feeling lonely or bored, without necessarily intending to rekindle a relationship.\n\n5. **Unresolved Feelings**: It's possible he hasn\u2019t fully moved on and is using these messages as a way to stay connected.\n\n6. **Mixed Signals**: He might be sending mixed signals, indicating that he\u2019s unsure about what he wants.\n\nIt's essential to consider how these interactions make you feel and whether you want to engage with him. Open communication can help clarify his intentions.",
